I paid a visit this afternoon to one of the areas in which a fence is being raised along the Egypt-Israel border. I received security briefings from the Deputy Chief of Staff of the IDF and from the Head of Southern Command.
 
We held a highly focused and effective discussion that will help lead this project to completion in the near future. This obstacle was designed to provide a response to the threat of border penetration. The fence is a good response to illegal work infiltrators, criminal smugglers and terror activists

צילום: עדי ברוך

מועצת זכויות האדם של האו"ם היא מועצה צבועה עם רוב אוטומטי נגד ישראל. עד היום היא קיבלה 91 החלטות: 39 מהן עסקו בישראל, 3 בסוריה ו-1 באיראן. די היה לשמוע את הנציג הסורי מדבר היום על זכויות אדם כדי להבין עד כמה המועצה מנותקת מהמציאות.

זו מועצה שצריכה להתבייש בעצמה, אין לה דבר וחצי דבר עם זכויות אדם.

The UN Human Rights Council is a hypocritical organization with an automatic anti-Israeli majority. To date, it has passed 91 resolutions: 39 of them on Israel, 3 on Syria and 1 on Iran. Just listening to the Syrian delegate speaking about human rights today was enough to show us how disconnected the Council is from reality. It's a council that should be ashamed of itself, and has nothing whatsoever to do with human rights

I paid a condolence visit this morning to the families of the Toulouse massacre victims. We all pray that the families will find the strength to handle their unspeakable pain. The State of Israel was founded to serve as the protector of the Jewish People
